{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/blog/20210101-learning-pixel-art/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Artem Demo, indie developer","author":"Artem Demo"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"ade981f3-fe22-587f-90dd-bbee0498b2a3","excerpt":"I decided to add diversity in everyday developers’ life and last month I started to learn a new thing - pixel art.\nIt was long waiting goal, but finally I found time to invest in it (thanks you to all lockdowns, I guess).","html":"<p>I decided to add diversity in everyday developers’ life and last month I started to learn a new thing - pixel art.\nIt was long waiting goal, but finally I found time to invest in it (thanks you to all lockdowns, I guess). </p>\n<!-- end -->\n<p>I don’t have well-defined goal or plan for this.\nI have some raw ideas in mind, will work on them in the upcoming months\nMeanwhile, it brings me joy, and I will stick with it for a while.</p>\n<p>By the way if you’re interested I started to learn with this two courses:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/course/pixel-art-for-video-games/\">https://www.udemy.com/course/pixel-art-for-video-games/</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/course/pixel-art-master-course/\">https://www.udemy.com/course/pixel-art-master-course/</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Not sure which one is better, check out both of them :)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/bbd2d4aeb3608b39e2bef5dc40da8590/b49bb/pixel-art.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 89.1891891891892%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"pixel art\"\n        title=\"pixel art\"\n        src=\"/static/bbd2d4aeb3608b39e2bef5dc40da8590/27330/pixel-art.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bbd2d4aeb3608b39e2bef5dc40da8590/3c361/pixel-art.png 148w,\n/static/bbd2d4aeb3608b39e2bef5dc40da8590/03654/pixel-art.png 295w,\n/static/bbd2d4aeb3608b39e2bef5dc40da8590/27330/pixel-art.png 590w,\n/static/bbd2d4aeb3608b39e2bef5dc40da8590/25849/pixel-art.png 885w,\n/static/bbd2d4aeb3608b39e2bef5dc40da8590/27179/pixel-art.png 1180w,\n/static/bbd2d4aeb3608b39e2bef5dc40da8590/b49bb/pixel-art.png 1495w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"I started to learn pixel art","date":"January 01, 2021","tags":["studying","pixel art"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/20210101-learning-pixel-art/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/20201029-adding-favicon-to-gatsby-site/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Adding favicon to gatsby website","tags":["favicon","gatsby"]}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/20210103-game-experiment/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"I started new game experiment","tags":["game","pixel art","unity"]}}}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}